  "title": "The Sith Dart Flowers",
  "summary": "Aboard the Imperial destroyer Predator, ISB Sector Director Korynn Fleming and the former Commodore Lynae Cassius confront one another in the Crew Commons, each weighing whether to bind themselves to a clandestine Sith order serving the Emperor Vadim. Darth Malign emerges from the shadows and, after silencing their bickering with a furious display of his authority, escorts the pair under droid guard into his Sith Meditation Chamber. There he reveals a galaxy map, a hidden facility being built beneath the broken world of Cochran, and a grove of sentient, poison-firing Sith dart flowers he intends to weaponize. Fleming swears immediate loyalty, but Lynae wavers, torn between the blood already on her hands, the seduction of returning home, and the unresolved love that anchors her elsewhere. Malign presses her with philosophy on fate, war, and humanity, recounting his own past as Tyler Damion, yet ultimately grants her leave to settle one final matter before giving her answer.",
